%spark2

import org.apache.spark.sql.hive.orc.OrcFileFormat

// Persist the user dataframe in query optimized format.
// ORC is a optimized file format for Apache Hive query.

// On FlashBlade, Spark can directly persist dataframe via S3A without issue. This is possible because FlashBlade supports strong consistency S3 implementation.
users.write.format("orc").mode("overwrite").save("s3a://yifeng-tweets/users-orc/")

// On Amazon S3 and many S3 compitable storage, it is not reliable to persisit dataframe directly.
// S3 is a eventual consistency model, which may cause some issue on the Spark save job. This limitation is true for most S3 compitable products including Amazone S3.
// Workaround is well-known. Firstly persist the dataframe to a temporary location on HDFS, once task completes, files are then uploaded to FlashBlade S3 bucket.

// users.write.format("orc").mode("overwrite").save("/tmp/users-orc/")
